                     <interp inst="t18280410-226-person1275" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-226-person1275" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Richard Hewitt, <rs id="t18280410-226-viclabel1208" type="occupation">cabinet-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-226-victim1274 t18280410-226-viclabel1208"></join> of Hammersmith. On the 21st of March, an alarm was given, and a piece of carpet was missed from the front of the shop; I ran out and took the prisoner, between three and four o'clock, at Kensington, with it - I did not see him till I got there; he had it under his left arm- I went up to him, and said I had every reason to believe it was masters; I secured him. I had seen it safe that morning; I left it at the watch-house with Mrs. Bennett.</p>
               <p>RICHARD HEWITT. This is my carpet. I went out about one o'clock, and left it safe then - I have a piece here, which matches it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-226-person1276">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BENNETT
               <interp inst="t18280410-226-person1276" type="surname" value="BENNETT"></interp>
